{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Truth_About_Lady_Alora",
  "title": "A Warning at the Palanhi Starport",
  "summary": "At the sun-baked Palanhi City Starport, Luke Skywalker tinkers with his astromech Artoo while finishing a repair job for a starstruck mechanic named Tand. The troubled Jessalyn Valios arrives from the Black Dragon to deliver an unsettling message: the night before she encountered the dark-side Force-wielder Lady Alora, who had probed her thoughts, claimed she needed Luke's help, and intended to meet with Leia. Luke, wary of Alora's trouble but believing she could still turn back from the Dark Side, presses Jessalyn for details. The conversation turns tender and painful as Jessalyn apologizes for the previous night and confesses feelings Luke gently insists he cannot return, for both their safety. Jessalyn then reveals that Alora had been tampering with Artoo, leaving the droid distressed, and Luke orders a diagnostic, fearing a tracking device, while Jessalyn crouches to examine and comfort the little astromech.",
